methods.applyAsInt:
Get the index of value in reverse lookup cache. Be sure to call ensurePopulated(int, Supplier, Consumer)
 for the appropriate index bound, first.

:param value: (ReverseOffsetLookupCache.VALUE_TYPE) - The value to look up
:return: (int) The index of value in the cache, or NULL_INDEX (-1) if not found
methods.clear: Release all resources held by the cache.
methods.ensurePopulated:
Ensure that the cache is populated for all indexes <= highestIndexNeeded.

:param highestIndexNeeded: (int) - The highest index needed for this operation
:param extraFactory: java.util.function.Supplier<ReverseOffsetLookupCache.EXTRA_INPUT_TYPE>
:param extraCleanup: java.util.function.Consumer<ReverseOffsetLookupCache.EXTRA_INPUT_TYPE>

text:
Caching data structure interface for caching Object to int (offset) mappings returned by an expensive, idempotent
 lookup function from int to Object.
